        content: `Swappa uses three condition grades: "Mint" means the phone looks and works like new with no visible wear; "Good" means minor cosmetic marks — tiny scratches on the back or around the screen — but full functionality; "Fair" means more visible wear such as scuffs or light scratches but still fully functional. These grades are self-reported by sellers but verified by Swappa's review team before the listing goes live. When buying, always read the seller's written description for specific details beyond just the grade.`,
