        content: `Clean the surface where you will attach the LED strip — use a dry cloth or a slightly damp paper towel and let it dry completely. Dust, grease, and moisture all weaken the adhesive backing and cause the strip to peel off over time. If you are attaching the strip behind a TV on an entertainment center, wipe the back edge of the unit clean. Measure the distance you want to cover before unrolling the strip — LED strips can be cut at marked intervals (look for the scissors icon printed on the strip) but cannot be extended without additional equipment.`,
        tip: `Quick Tip: The adhesive on LED strips is permanent once fully pressed — plan your layout before peeling the backing. Lay the strip along the surface dry first to confirm placement, then peel and press.`,
